author: Times-News
title: Duke women capture Landfall Tradition title
text: Posted Oct. 26, 2015 at 12:25 AM Updated at 12:27 AM Posted Oct. 26, 2015 at 12:25 AM Updated at 12:27 AM WILMINGTON — The Duke women’s golf team was under par for all three rounds, clinching the Landfall Tradition title Sunday at the Country Club of Landfall’s Pete Dye Course. Duke’s 855 total gave the Blue Devils an 11-shot edge on runner-up Notre Dame. North Carolina State (885) was sixth, Wake Forest (886) placed seventh, UNC Wilmington (889) tied for 10th and North Carolina (901) was 14th. Elon (927) placed last in the 18-team field. It was the second team victory during the fall season for Duke. Celine Boutier of Duke placed fourth at 3-under 213 with rounds of 75, 69 and 69. The individual champion was Michigan State’s Sarah Burnham at 5-under, one shot better than Central Florida’s Ashley Holder and South Carolina’s Katelyn Dambaugh. Elon’s Kelsey Badmaev tied for 42nd at 9-over (77, 76, 72). By Times-News
